ucscphastConsChIP-seqpeak bedRpythonRconservation profile

Requirement Description

Input phastCons file on ucsc, peak bed file on ChIP-seq. Calculate values in R or python, draw conservation profile in R

https://www.nature.com/articles/ncomms7315

fromhttps://www.nature.com/articles/ncomms7315

Application Scenarios

Demonstrate the conserved nature of specific regions.

Important regions tend to be highly conserved, such as transcription factor binding sites.

getBigWigValue.py

Extracting signals

Write a function that calls getBigWigValue.py, located in the current folder.

regionCapture <- function(seqname, start, end, bw, datapoints, captureMethod="security", cores=4L) {
  # bigwig / Capture bigwig signals in genomic regions
  #  / Parameters:
  #   seqname -  / Vector of chromosome names
  #   start -  / Vector of start positions
  #   end -  / Vector of end positions  
  #   bw - bigwig / Path to bigwig file
  #   datapoints -  / Number of datapoints per region
  #   captureMethod - "security" / Calculation method, default "security"
  #   cores - CPU4 / Number of CPU cores to use, default 4
  
  # BED / Create BED format region file
  captureRegion <- data.frame(seqname=seqname, start=start, end=end)
  write.table(captureRegion, file="captureRegion.bed", 
              quote=FALSE, sep="\t", row.names=FALSE, col.names=FALSE)
  
  # Pythonbigwig / Call Python script to process bigwig file
  suppressMessages(
    system(paste("python getBigWigValue.py -b", "captureRegion.bed", 
                "-w", bw, "-n regionCapture", 
                "-p", cores, "-s", datapoints, 
                "-m", captureMethod))
  )
  
  #  / Read processed results
  signal <- read.table(gzfile("signal_regionCapture_siteprof1.gz"))
  
  return(signal)
}

signal_caputer_around_sites <- function(bigWigFile, bed, resolution=50, 
                                       span=3000, captureMethod="security", 
                                       cores=4L) {
  #  / Calculate average signals around sites
  #  / Parameters:
  #   bigWigFile - bigwig / Path to bigwig file
  #   bed - BED / BED format dataframe
  #   resolution - (bp)50 / Resolution in bp, default 50
  #   span - (bp)3000 / Analysis span in bp, default 3000
  #   captureMethod - "security" / Calculation method, default "security"
  #   cores - CPU4 / Number of CPU cores, default 4
  
  #  / Calculate total datapoints
  datapoints <- span * 2 / resolution + 1  #  / Including center point
  
  #  / Extract chromosome names
  seqname <- bed[,1]
  
  #  / Calculate site center positions
  midpoints <- as.integer((bed[,2] + bed[,3] - 1) / 2)  # BED0-based / BED is 0-based
  
  #  / Get strand information
  if(ncol(bed) > 5) { 
    strand <- bed[,6]  # 6 / Column 6 contains strand info
  } else {
    strand <- rep(".", nrow(bed))  #  / Default no strand info
  }
  
  #  / Capture signals
  signal <- regionCapture(seqname, 
                         midpoints-span-resolution/2,  #  / Start position
                         midpoints+span+resolution/2,  #  / End position
                         bigWigFile, datapoints, captureMethod, cores)
  
  #  / Correct strand orientation & calculate average signal
  write.table(signal, file="temp_signal.txt", 
             quote=FALSE, row.names=FALSE, col.names=FALSE, sep="\t")
  write.table(strand, file="temp_strand.txt", 
             quote=FALSE, row.names=FALSE, col.names=FALSE, sep="\t")
  
  # awk / Use awk to process reverse strand signals
  system(paste0("paste temp_signal.txt temp_strand.txt | awk '{if($NF==",
               '"',"+",'"',") {for(i=1;i<NF-1;i++) printf $i",
               '"',"\t",'"',"; print $(NF-1)} else {for(i=NF-1;i>1;i--) printf $i",
               '"',"\t",'"',"; print $1}}' > temp_signal_rev.txt"))
  
  # data.table / Use data.table for efficient reading
  signal_rev <- data.table::fread("temp_signal_rev.txt")
  
  #  / Clean up temporary files
  file.remove("temp_signal.txt")
  file.remove("temp_strand.txt") 
  file.remove("temp_signal_rev.txt")
  
  #  / Return average signals at each position
  return(apply(signal_rev, 2, mean))
}

Extract the signal

#  / Initialize average signal matrix
# BED / To store results from all BED files
average_signal <- c()

# BED / Loop through each BED file
for(i in 1:length(bedFiles)) {
  
  # BED / Load BED file
  # bedFilesBED / bedFiles is a character vector containing paths to multiple BED files
  bed <- read.table(bedFiles[i])
  
  #  / Filter non-standard chromosomes
  # (chr1, chrX) / Keep only standard chromosomes without underscores (e.g. chr1, chrX)
  # "chrUn_" / Note: Some genomes may contain "chrUn_" or random chromosomes
  isNormalChrosome <- !grepl("_", bed$V1)  # V1 / Column V1 is usually chromosome name
  bed <- bed[isNormalChrosome, ]
  
  #  / Capture signals around sites and store results
  # signal_caputer_around_sitesBED / Process each BED file using signal_caputer_around_sites function
  average_signal <- rbind(average_signal, 
                         signal_caputer_around_sites(
                           bigWigFile = bigWigFile,  #  / Conservation score file
                           bed = bed,                # BED / Current BED file data
                           resolution = resolution,  #  / Analysis resolution
                           span = span,              #  / Analysis span
                           captureMethod = captureMethod,  #  / Calculation method
                           cores = as.integer(coreNumber)  #  / Number of cores for parallel computing
                         ))
  
  #  / Optional progress message
  if(i %% 1 == 0) {  # 1 / Show progress after each file
    message(" ", i, "/", length(bedFiles), " (", round(i/length(bedFiles)*100, 1), "%)")
    utils::flush.console()  #  / Ensure immediate message display
  }
}

#  / Load saved average signal data
average_signal <- read.csv("average_signal.csv")

#  / Preview beginning and end of data
head(average_signal[,c(1:3,(ncol(average_signal)-2):ncol(average_signal))])
##          V1        V2        V3      V199      V200      V201
## 1 0.1150350 0.1154582 0.1176155 0.1185914 0.1161026 0.1148453
## 2 0.1150350 0.1154582 0.1176155 0.1185914 0.1161026 0.1148453
## 3 0.1137995 0.1176929 0.1165951 0.1196118 0.1138679 0.1160808
# 33 / Shows first 3 and last 3 columns
#  / Helps check data range and integrity

# Y / Set y-axis display range
minimum <- min(average_signal) - (max(average_signal) - min(average_signal)) * 0.1
# 10% / Extend 10% below minimum
maximum <- max(average_signal) + (max(average_signal) - min(average_signal)) * 0.1 * length(bedFiles)
# 10% / Extend 10%number of samples above maximum

#  / Calculate number of datapoints
datapoints <- span / resolution  #  / Datapoints on one side

#  / Create graphic output
# pdf(outputName, width = 6, height = 5)  #  / Commented out, uncomment for actual use

#  () / Plot first line (baseline)
plot(1:(datapoints*2+1),  # X / X-axis positions
     average_signal[1,],   # Y / Y-axis values
     type="l",             #  / Line plot
     lwd = 2,              #  / Line width
     col=colors[1],        #  / Color
     xaxs="i", yaxs="i",   #  / Axes fit data range exactly
     xaxt="n",             # X / Temporarily disable x-axis
     xlab=paste("Distance from", siteType),  # X / X-axis label
     ylab="Average PhastCons score",         # Y / Y-axis label
     ylim=c(minimum, maximum))              # Y / Y-axis range

#  / Add lines for other samples
for(i in 2:length(bedFiles)){
  lines(1:(datapoints*2+1), 
        average_signal[i,], 
        lwd = 2, 
        col=colors[i])  #  / Use predefined colors
}

#  / Add legend
legend("topright",         #  / Legend position
       col=colors,         #  / Colors
       legend=labels,      #  / Label text
       lty=1,              #  / Line type
       lwd = 2,            #  / Line width
       bty="n")            #  / No border

# X / Customize x-axis
axis(side=1,  # X / Bottom x-axis
     at=c(0, datapoints, datapoints * 2) + 1,  #  / Tick positions
     labels = c(paste(-1*span/1000,"kb"),       #  / Left label
               "0",                             #  / Center point
               paste(span/1000,"kb")))          #  / Right label
